Sure, that’s what restauranteurs do, but this one has twice the amount of rice as any other place.  PLUS, their scallop was not fresh at all.  No, I would not post any of this, but the next thing pushed me over the top. For our second round, I explained the scallop issue and how there is too much rice. Guess what they came back with? Take a look at the attached photo, 66% less fish but 20% less rice.  So, in the end, it’s confirmed. They just want to trick u and stuff u with rice. I will NEVER go back. We were used to coming here every month for all you can eat sushi and always enjoyed our experience with food and staff. Last time we went there for our anniversary it was all new staff. My girlfriend started a new diet and she couldn't eat rice. We inquired about sashimi all you can eat option upon arrival. The tall waitress girl (don't know her name since didn't introduce herself) right away responded with a "no". We asked her to check with cheff, which she unwillingly did and said it would be $50 for sashimi (regular sushi option is $22) to which we agreed, but which is I still think overpriced. Waitress wouldn't even look at us while taking an order for soup/salad and drinks. Upon bringing the order she knocked the tea cup over which almost spilled on my girlfriend and made a big mess under the table. She didn't apologize and threw a napkin under the table to cover up the mess. We were sitting in that mess for 10 minutes until I finally approached her and asked her if she could mop up the spill. She rolled her eyes but came back and cleaned up the mess. While we were eating our "all you can eat" my girlfriend offered me a piece of her sashimi to taste. The waitress saw it and when she brought a check $6 was added to our $72 plus tax bill. I inquired about an extra charge to which she replied "you can't share your food", remember we both ordered all you can eat (plus extra $28 for sashimi option). I told her it didn't make sense, she returned with another check with $2 added instead of $6. I asked another girl at the register about the extra charge to which she blamed it on a cheff and when I asked to speak with the manager she said she can remove the charge but "it will be on your consciousness".  Note to management: hire people who demonstrate respect and courtesy especially if they work in hospitality!
